                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.51/726</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Alternate Chairman of the International Committee of Bankers on Mexico</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">T. W. Lamont</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lamont</hi>: I have received your letter of
                    June 27th and have considered the proposed response to the invitation extended
                    to you by the Mexican regime.</p>
                <p>I think that the proposed communication to the Mexican Chargé at Washington, who
                    presented the invitation to you, is admirable and it has my approval.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles E. Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
